suspend(25.10)                                                  suspend(25.10)

Name
       suspend - Suspends your script and returns to the Innovus prompt

Syntax
       suspend [-help]

       Suspends your script and returns to the Innovus prompt.

       The  suspend  command gives you more flexibility in managing and debug-
       ging your scripts. You  can  insert  multiple  suspend  commands  in  a
       script.  The  suspend  command can also be used in nested scripts. When
       the script reaches a point where you have inserted the suspend command,
       it stops and restores access to the Innovus prompt. You can  then  type
       any command required for debugging.

       Whenever  you  want  to resume your script, just type resume at the In-
       novus prompt.

Parameters
       -help  Prints the usage of the suspend command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man  command:
              man suspend.

Related Information
              * resume

              * "Interrupting  the  Software"  section  of the Getting Started
                chapter in the Innovus User Guide

